00:18:20,583 --> 00:18:22,916
requires a great
deal of computation.

311
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:25,458
Naturally, it's not possible
to coordinate the tasks

312
00:18:25,541 --> 00:18:27,250
over a large
network without some

313
00:18:27,333 --> 00:18:29,708
sort of grid computing
and middleware.

314
00:18:29,791 --> 00:18:31,750
But the more I investigated,

315
00:18:31,833 --> 00:18:35,541
the more I realized the flow
of the data was clearly strange.

316
00:18:35,625 --> 00:18:36,916
You have the scanners
throughout town,

317
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:41,083
the authorized counseling
AIs, and the Dominators.

318
00:18:41,166 --> 00:18:45,041
At first the data appeared to be
processed throughout the grid,

319
00:18:45,125 --> 00:18:46,416
but it was actually
just being passed

320
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:48,958
from one place to
another untouched.

321
00:18:49,041 --> 00:18:52,625
All these processors
exchanging data,

322
00:18:52,708 --> 00:18:55,375
but none of them actually
doing the processing.

323
00:18:55,458 --> 00:18:56,791
Then I found something.

324
00:18:56,875 --> 00:18:58,791
A single relay point
that every communication

325
00:18:58,875 --> 00:19:00,625
goes through at least once.

326
00:19:00,708 --> 00:19:02,916
If a stand-alone system
the public doesn't know

327
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:05,958
about is carefully hidden
at that relay point.

328
00:19:06,041 --> 00:19:08,041
And that one secret
machine is managing

329
00:19:08,125 --> 00:19:11,166
all of Sibyl's processing
and computation.

330
00:19:11,250 --> 00:19:13,583
Then suddenly it makes sense.

331
00:19:13,666 --> 00:19:16,291
I always knew you
were a genius, Choe.

332
00:19:16,375 --> 00:19:19,416
Well, it makes sense
logically, that is.

333
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:22,000
But there are still a ton
of mysteries to unravel.

334
00:19:22,083 --> 00:19:23,291
Like its capacity.

335
00:19:23,375 --> 00:19:24,875
If it's really a
stand-alone system,

336
00:19:24,958 --> 00:19:27,583
it's exhibiting a throughput
that's not possible

337
00:19:27,666 --> 00:19:29,500
with existing technologies.

338
00:19:29,583 --> 00:19:32,625
And then there's
the question of why.

